result.name: Teppanyaki Sessyu

reviews.text: Amazing cuisine, top quality ingredients prepared by skillful chef. The experience doesn't come cheap but it worth every penny. Negative point will be the wine list with far too many wines out of stock. We visited in late May 19, they were due to launch a new wine list in the coming weeks.
Nice staff but food was top bland for my taste. Restaurant is quite expensive. For a teppanyaki restaurant this place didn’t have enough flavor and was a big disappointment for us.

It’s our first time to this restaurant. 
Place was spacious, clean, nicely decorated and with good ambient. 

We ordered our dinner and the first dish was salad with truffle. My friend happened to have truffle allergy. So the staffs (chefs, waiters) asked us and make sure my friend has no other allergy and immediately created another dish. Efficient, caring and creative. 

My friend particularly like all the utensils served. Chef was 100% on our meal only. (No need for sharing chef). The food was fresh and cooked just right, so delicious that I felt I melt with the foie quis. 

Sake and dessert were amazing as well. Portion was all good, not too much not too less. 

The whole meal was amazing.
Everything just right - the Tapanyaki master was attentive and making good recommendation. Upgraded the meal to include the Australian Beef. Tasty and alright. 👌👌😉
Great food and service
